* Main program testing channel separation and reconciliation (FR-17, NFR-6, M-6)
*
* Statements below cover all six cases for corpus reconciliation:
* 1. Resolvable static call → resolution outcome (Resolved)
* 2. Dynamic call → resolution outcome (Unresolved-dynamic)
* 3. Literal call with no target → resolution outcome (Unresolved-no-target)
* 4. Ambiguous call (duplicate name in flat namespace) → resolution outcome (Ambiguous) + 1 diagnostic
* 5. Placeholder call → resolution outcome (Unresolved-dynamic)
* 6. Malformed statement (no operand) → parser diagnostic ONLY, no resolution edge

DEFINE DATA
LOCAL
1 #VAR (A5)
END-DEFINE

*> Case 1: resolvable static call
CALLNAT 'GOODSUB'

*> Case 2: dynamic call
CALLNAT #VAR

*> Case 3: literal with no matching object
CALLNAT 'NOSUCH'

*> Case 4: ambiguous call (duplicate in flat namespace)
CALLNAT 'DUPLICATE-NAME'

*> Case 5: placeholder literal → already dynamic at extraction
CALLNAT 'PRG&X'

*> Case 6: genuinely malformed — bare CALLNAT with no operand
CALLNAT

END-PROGRAM.
